<h3>How does it work?</h3>
<p>If you have a simple Software as a service (Saas), a website or even a mobile app idea I usually go with a workflow that follows Lean Startup Methodology and spend as little cash as possible (hence all the free tools). Below how I utilize all the tools in sequence to effectively launch an idea within a week, then test and iterate the product idea based on users feedback. Creating a simple landing page and email/social media automation might not be the most effective way to launch an MVP, but definitely the cheapest &amp; fastest method that requires the least technical skills </p>
<p>If there are no competitors in the space, I would try to find if there is a demand for your idea. A good place to start would be Google Trends that lets you see the brief quantity of your search terms</p>
<p> After a few weeks of testing and talking to customers (in real life or online, depending on your idea) You should be able to tell if you would like to commit to the idea. If you do, I would find a technical cofounder that could create the product and start investing either your own savings or a F&amp;F rounds (friends &amp; Family rounds). If you haven't already, I'd recommend you getting the book 'Lean Startup' by Eric Ries, the most comprehensive book to date on starting a startup.</p>
